description: A rocket strike has killed at least 11 people in Syria’s Israeli-occupied Golan Heights, prompting the Israeli regime to blame Hezbollah for the attack, despite the Lebanese resistance group’s strong denial of any role in the incident.
title: Rocket strike kills 11 in Israeli-occupied Golan Heights

description: TEHRAN – 70 foreign delegates, including 10 presidents and primes ministers, will participate in the inauguration of Iranian President-elect Masoud Pezeshkian on Tuesday.
title: 70 foreign delegates to attend inauguration of Iranian president

description: TEHRAN – Ecbatana, a treasured ancient city of Iran known for its profound historical and cultural significance, has been officially inscribed on the World Heritage List by the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO).
title: Iran's Ecbatana added to UNESCO World Heritage list

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s president-elect Masoud Pezeshkian has sent a message to the Bahraini king thanking him for his congratulatory message over his presidential win.
title: Pezeshkian thanks Bahraini king for congratulatory message

description: TEHRAN - Iran is the top country among Islamic nations for the number of publications in water science and technology, the head of the Islamic World Science Citation (ISC) Institute has said.
title: Iran ranks first among Islamic nations for publications in water science and technology

description: Israeli air strikes on a girls' school in Deir al-Balah, central Gaza, killed at least 30 people and wounded over 100 on Saturday, the Palestinian health ministry said.
title: Israeli strike on girls' school in Gaza kills at least 30 displaced people

description: Mossad chief David Barnea is expected to travel to Rome on Sunday to meet with CIA director William Burns, Qatari Prime Minister Mohammed bin Abdulrahman al-Thani and head of Egyptian intelligence Abbas Kamel to continue talks on a potential deal that would see the release of the hostages and a ceasefire in Gaza, Al Monitor reported on Friday.
title: Egypt, Qatar, US, and Israel to discuss Gaza truce in Rome

description: TEHRAN – The number of persons drowned since the beginning of the current Iranian calendar year (March 19) has increased by 15 percent compared to the same period in the previous year.
title: Drowning increases since mid-March yr/yr

description: Italy will soon send an ambassador to Syria, the country’s top diplomat said on Friday, in a boost for Syrian President Bashar al-Assad in his quest for international legitimacy as well as Italy's efforts to stop migration into Europe.
title: Italy appoints ambassador to Syria in latest sign of European thaw

description: Vice President Kamala Harris says she will “not be silent” in the face of Palestinian suffering, as Israel’s war in Gaza rages on.
title: Kamala Harris shifts tone on Gaza, but voters want more

description: Foreign ministers of the Southeast Asian regional bloc ASEAN have expressed “grave concern over the dire humanitarian situation in Gaza”.
title: ASEAN foreign ministers call for Gaza truce

description: TEHRAN – In the past Iranian calendar year that ended on March 19, mangrove forests in the southern parts of the country were expanded by 267 hectares, an official with the Department of Environment has said.
title: Mangrove forests expanded by 267 hectares in a year

description: TEHRAN – Iran defeated Kazakhstan in straight sets (25-21, 25-16, 25-22) in the 2024 Asian Men's U20 Volleyball Championship on Saturday.
title: Iran victorious over Kazakhstan in 2024 Asian U20 Volleyball Championship
